snippet.textDisplay: Se la dedique a una persona muy especial, pensando que trataba de algo diferente. Ahora entiendo mejor la letra gracias al video. La chica a quien le dedique esta canción era suicida, desde que la conocí me encariñe demasiado con ella. Quería entenderla y ayudarla en lo que pudiera, siempre intentaba dar lo mejor de mi para hacerla sonreír y que olvidara todos sus problemas. Aunque a veces pensaba que no hacía suficiente. Siempre viví con el miedo de que en algún momento tomara la decisión equivocada y no poder impedir que sucediera. Gracias a Dios sigue viva y espero que se quede conmigo por un largo tiempo.

snippet.textDisplay: I can relate this song to my life. I was tried to committing suicide when I was 14 years old because I lost my father when I was 8 years then  I lost my little sister 2 years after my father died. I was so depressed I was antisocial I didn't feel like I deserved to live. I hate myself I hate my life. The thing that changes my life was starting writing poems. To transfer all this pain all this darkness inside me to write it in piece of paper it really felt for the first time the peace inside me. Doing new things like doing covers it really made start believing in myself. I started to do covers the first cover I done was Someone you loved by Lewis Capaldi. I actually met Lewis Capaldi himself in his concert in Sharjah he really liked my cover even though I was in some places out of the key, but suprisely he liked it and he told to keep going and never stop trying and keep practicing it. It was the best day in my life ♥️♥️♥️♥️♥️

snippet.textDisplay:
Chills... 😭❤️

My friend committed suicide almost 3 years ago now and this song just hits me right in the heart. None of us ever knew he was struggling with anything and then out of no where he was just gone. All I think about now is how I should have been closer to him, I should have talked to him more, I should have been there. I can feel his spirit in the girl in this video and how he always loved having fun and then how we all felt when he was gone. A bunch of 15 year olds should not have had to go through that... this world just sucks... Thank you Lewis for giving everyone who is struggling something amazing like this. I will always thank God that I was able to have known my friend and that I was born in the same lifetime as you. ❤️
